<worksheet xml:id="activity-01-intro-activity" xmlns:xi="http://w3.org">
    <title>01. Activity Voting Methods</title>

  <!-- Optional introduction -->
  <introduction>
    <p>
      In many decision making situations, it is necessary to gather the group consensus 
      using some sort of vote. While the basic idea of voting is fairly universal, 
      the method by which those votes are used to determine a winner can vary. 
      In deciding upon a winner, there is always one main goal: to reflect the preferences 
      of the people in the most fair way possible. We will discuss four different methods 
      for determining the winner of an election using preference ballots, and will see that 
      we can sometimes have different winners under different methods of voting. 
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <p>See <xref ref="notes-Voting" /> for the voting notes.</p>

